</p></li><li id="LI_50E213EF99904105955A3A2C23FCE763" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Open the top cover. 
</p><note type="important" id="GUID-7215619B-4D8E-42B1-B219-10C1EF6B5FB5" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">Do not lean on the strip support. 
</p></note></li><li id="LI_B3070DDF7AFE4B65BF4A8343C06C58BE" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the maintenance tray. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">See : 
<xref keyref="07DISA020" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-C04E8AED-532E-4792-9B1F-478E74979222.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 07 How to remove the maintenance tray?>07 How to remove the maintenance tray</xref> 
</p></li><li id="LI_8EFCF849C54841B08EA90E712816C8E3" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the maintenance tray assembly. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">See : 
<xref keyref="07DISA022" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-2D90D262-D1D0-4062-B2F5-28ED447BF111.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 07 How to remove the maintenance tray assembly?>07 How to remove the maintenance tray assembly</xref> 
</p></li><li id="LI_4A5292BCDE6D4A1F8BF3EC341C13C4BB" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the maintenance unit. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">See : 
<xref keyref="07DISA024" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-17B27C06-4881-45FC-A784-579CC398D058.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 07 How to remove the maintenance unit?>07 How to remove the Tissue Wipe Unit</xref> 
</p></li></ol></prereq><section id="GUID-E4895B67-7FC1-4974-A5C8-D34725505879" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Required tools</title><ul id="UL_A32A562039FB485780CA65B069EE577C" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_1D9EE245DE6547E09D8CB22E45CFC7A0" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Screwdriver Torx T10. 
</p></li><li id="LI_55373F9DAE644089ABBC568E03CDE4FC" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Screwdriver Torx T20. 
</p></li><li id="LI_929C0F12811B4096BB70DA320BD9C6C8" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Protective gloves : 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Microflex</b> 93-260 gloves. 
</p></li></ul></section><section id="GUID-C02D66D1-E3CC-4BC2-95F8-775D93D93431" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Warning / Caution</title><note type="caution" id="GUID-A97040BC-F110-4E4B-9CFF-E8082B9DA00E" class="- topic/note "><fig id="GUID-9848D934-FF3E-4AC9-BA07-69028FA44036" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-FCF86E23-0DD4-40BC-ACDF-FF8ABA1E6502-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-FCF86E23-0DD4-40BC-ACDF-FF8ABA1E6502-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">Avoid skin contact with ink: wear protective gloves. 
</p><fig id="GUID-7C716739-2AD7-42F8-8EF6-B28A8E7B1F76" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-D8099BBE-C3A2-4392-8B56-C532EDDD6073-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-D8099BBE-C3A2-4392-8B56-C532EDDD6073-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p "> Protect your eyes from splashing ink: wear safety glasses. 
</p></note><note type="important" id="GUID-985FFBF4-CACE-47F4-AF21-7A7BEBBB34EA" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">Use an antistatic wrist strap. 
</p></note></section><section id="GUID-EC9C24D5-D455-4022-B616-D7FEF4DE0A1A" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Illustration</title><fig id="GUID-1C6A5506-8461-4BFD-8B7C-FB47C7EF289A" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-A8180001-79A0-49E3-9379-9093EAC13A81-low.png" id="IMAGE_5529F665C0DF414FA1E3B14FDB962D0C" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-A8180001-79A0-49E3-9379-9093EAC13A81-low.png"/></fig><fig id="FIG_EC104C9C005E41AD99F2DD1917A4FE0A" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-F0157BEC-BB0E-42EE-B7A6-5C8C2CF67975-low.png" id="IMAGE_59FFA5C3CA3F49FC94D7AD99081AAE4D" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-F0157BEC-BB0E-42EE-B7A6-5C8C2CF67975-low.png"/></fig></section><section id="SECTION_676D8E59167F4927BAACAD2565440469" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">How to remove</title><table pgwide="1" id="TABLE_FDD8FD89D6E5405B860B62D2D8C2CE6D" class="- topic/table "><tgroup align="left" outputclass="step" cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="40*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead valign="top" class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remarks 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody valign="top" class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the Xtran Drive Assembly Cover by removing 1 Torx T20 screw. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Loosen 2 screws to remove the tension of the (upper) drive belt. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_3934C14409AF4F6896FA77D55B92B59A" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-93FC21F1-39AE-4BD3-98CC-E7FDCEF5AD7A-low.png" id="IMAGE_BE0660AC6F364092B0802E8F24B2A22E" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-93FC21F1-39AE-4BD3-98CC-E7FDCEF5AD7A-low.png"/></fig><fig id="FIG_8500DB0E713B44A09FBBCC4CB66250B2" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-7AA592D4-9432-4271-A301-DE6947DEA875-low.png" id="IMAGE_15A7C47298E64B1F8B37B5A1965E82B6" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-7AA592D4-9432-4271-A301-DE6947DEA875-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the 4 screws. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_23B0F83F76174D639C4F15082A51D189" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-511003EC-DE9F-4911-963B-92F41893C3C8-low.png" id="IMAGE_F5C310508E4E4596B3FCDC2BDA353A5C" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-511003EC-DE9F-4911-963B-92F41893C3C8-low.png"/></fig><fig id="FIG_3EB7C5C2F5E24A90B679A9231E7BF740" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-C3B4157F-F855-4507-BCC3-103D08824664-low.png" id="IMAGE_BF9C5D3E82674AEDB999FBDEA9451446" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-C3B4157F-F855-4507-BCC3-103D08824664-low.png"/></fig><fig id="FIG_6DDB2E1BC4464B669FB5A2CEE2440FE5" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-D0D8E28E-7AC7-4728-92A0-F0921F648189-low.png" id="IMAGE_D5DA27B82EEF40C0B1C70F17CB477491" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-D0D8E28E-7AC7-4728-92A0-F0921F648189-low.png"/></fig><fig id="FIG_B02C6DEFAA134C3092F710D7EFB4A2C9" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-5BD97EF9-628D-48B1-A2A1-99B475831329-low.png" id="IMAGE_64E7D4A8ABB74DE8B4AF11005E84A18B" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-5BD97EF9-628D-48B1-A2A1-99B475831329-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Remove the X motion system drive roll encoder 15B4 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the drive belt from the gear (of Xtran roller). 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_C649F9E80DDC4AA3BDAE192107BE0316" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-17B26A8F-C176-4F29-B823-F3CEB70BC573-low.png" id="IMAGE_737DA9E87E9F46B4BBF2D5806D27151B" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-17B26A8F-C176-4F29-B823-F3CEB70BC573-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">5 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Take out the Xtran drive assembly. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_CD1593A8B3CD4B829E31F4AF08593B2E" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-4B6FF960-CE12-42F6-B606-AF32149C87D2-low.png" id="IMAGE_BD6F6F90660942D49C242559A2E44437" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-4B6FF960-CE12-42F6-B606-AF32149C87D2-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">6 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Disconnect the connector of the motor sensor. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_6B18499C28134ABC9BD44ACCC7F5284D" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-72D897BF-1A92-49DD-B0CD-796A86CBB110-low.png" id="IMAGE_A9C99EA078584784A8A42986492B5C6C" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-72D897BF-1A92-49DD-B0CD-796A86CBB110-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">7 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Take out the assembly. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_18C89779F6794C5B8F4D44A348D81F69" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-317AC7F9-B54D-4142-A433-74074BE23586-low.png" id="IMAGE_7BF34A30FFD74CB5896279A349B99A3C" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-317AC7F9-B54D-4142-A433-74074BE23586-low.png"/></fig><fig id="FIG_BB8713A819014FF2B33072513697540B" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-F0157BEC-BB0E-42EE-B7A6-5C8C2CF67975-low.png" id="IMAGE_6E923947B9CE469897E50019992260EA" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-F0157BEC-BB0E-42EE-B7A6-5C8C2CF67975-low.png"/></fig></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-234D70A5-41EC-40E2-9E43-4217D346F540" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">How to install</title><table pgwide="1" id="TABLE_A7B7F2276EC64F88A303AD9C9A521E96" class="- topic/table "><tgroup align="left" outputclass="step" cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="40*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead valign="top" class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remarks 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody valign="top" class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Install in reverse order. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Reconnect the Service jumper, exit SDS and press 'Restart' on the operator panel. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Always do the following calibration : 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Do 
<xref keyref="SDS21-6-002" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-D650BDBB-4674-4B96-BD64-98FDD9BAF4CB.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 21-6-002 Select required printer calibrations [Special Tests]?>21-6-002 Select required printer calibrations [Special Tests]</xref> and select: <ph translate="no" class="- topic/ph ">Media transport calibration</ph> 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Do 
<xref keyref="SDS21-6-003" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-B828E436-A124-4809-981E-2DBE1E09A388.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 21-6-003 Execute selected printer calibrations [Special Tests]?>21-6-003 Execute selected printer calibrations [Special Tests]</xref> 
</p></li></ul></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-027A0565-F050-4419-9B19-C5C075964C5A.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Dis-assembly</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
